 This function checks if all the numbers in a list are less than or equal to a given threshold. It returns True if all the numbers are less than or equal to the threshold and False otherwise. The code is as follows:
```php
function belowThreshold($l, $t) {
    foreach ($l as $number) {
        if ($number > $t) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}
```
This function iterates through the list and checks each number. If any of them is greater than the threshold, it returns False. Otherwise, it returns True.

